{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a1d08665a97a4c22", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# Vox-Evaluator: Enhancing Stability and Fidelity for Zero-shot TTS with A Multi-Level Evaluator\narXiv: 2510.20210\nAuthors: Hualei Wang, Na Li, Chuke Wang, Shu Wu, Zhifeng Li, Dong Yu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a novel multi-level Vox-Evaluator that provides a comprehensive evaluation of the generated speech for the correction process and fine-grained guidance for preference alignment.\n  2. We utilize a speech correction mechanism based on the Vox-Evaluator to enhance the stability of zero-shot TTS systems and provide effective guidance for preference alignment.\n  3. We demonstrate through experiments on different zero-shot TTS frameworks that the Vox-Evaluator effectively facilitates the stability and fidelity of the TTS model.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/功能-语音编辑, Eval, Eval/学习\n---\n# Beyond Global Emotion: Fine-Grained Emotional Speech Synthesis with Dynamic Word-Level Modulation\narXiv: 2509.20378\nAuthors: Sirui Wang, Andong Chen, Tiejun Zhao\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose Emo-FiLM, a fine-grained emotion modeling framework for LLM-based TTS that achieves dynamic word-level emotion control beyond global sentence-level signals.\n  2. We introduce a method to align frame-level features from emotion2vec with words to generate detailed word-level emotion annotations.\n  3. We design an Emotion Feature-wise Linear Modulation (E-FiLM) layer that transforms word-level emotion signals into scale and shift parameters to directly modulate text embeddings.\n  4. We construct the Fine-grained Emotion Dynamics Dataset (FEDD) to provide detailed annotations of emotional transitions for evaluating fine-grained emotion modeling.\n  5. We demonstrate through experiments that Emo-FiLM outperforms existing approaches on both global and fine-grained emotional speech synthesis tasks.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/控制-风格标签", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "15b66e3c-24ae-4c4d-878e-fff4af0e2688", "uuid": "89f0098a-2b31-4d76-a842-fdf26a12ab33", "timestamp": "2026-07-21T07:10:46.932Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# Vox-Evaluator: Enhancing Stability and Fidelity for Zero-shot TTS with A Multi-Level Evaluator\narXiv: 2510.20210\nAuthors: Hualei Wang, Na Li, Chuke Wang, Shu Wu, Zhifeng Li, Dong Yu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a novel multi-level Vox-Evaluator that provides a comprehensive evaluation of the generated speech for the correction process and fine-grained guidance for preference alignment.\n  2. We utilize a speech correction mechanism based on the Vox-Evaluator to enhance the stability of zero-shot TTS systems and provide effective guidance for preference alignment.\n  3. We demonstrate through experiments on different zero-shot TTS frameworks that the Vox-Evaluator effectively facilitates the stability and fidelity of the TTS model.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/功能-语音编辑, Eval, Eval/学习\n---\n# Beyond Global Emotion: Fine-Grained Emotional Speech Synthesis with Dynamic Word-Level Modulation\narXiv: 2509.20378\nAuthors: Sirui Wang, Andong Chen, Tiejun Zhao\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose Emo-FiLM, a fine-grained emotion modeling framework for LLM-based TTS that achieves dynamic word-level emotion control beyond global sentence-level signals.\n  2. We introduce a method to align frame-level features from emotion2vec with words to generate detailed word-level emotion annotations.\n  3. We design an Emotion Feature-wise Linear Modulation (E-FiLM) layer that transforms word-level emotion signals into scale and shift parameters to directly modulate text embeddings.\n  4. We construct the Fine-grained Emotion Dynamics Dataset (FEDD) to provide detailed annotations of emotional transitions for evaluating fine-grained emotion modeling.\n  5. We demonstrate through experiments that Emo-FiLM outperforms existing approaches on both global and fine-grained emotional speech synthesis tasks.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/控制-风格标签", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
